# Netlify Deployment Standard

All websites must use this Netlify setup for consistent deployment via `netlify deploy --prod`.

## next.config.js / next.config.ts

- Add `eslint: { ignoreDuringBuilds: true }` so lint warnings don't fail the build
- Do NOT use `output: "export"` – use full Next.js runtime (Netlify OpenNext handles it)
- Do NOT use `output: "standalone"` – that's for Vercel/Docker

```js
// next.config.js
const nextConfig = {
  eslint: { ignoreDuringBuilds: true },
};
```

## netlify.toml

```toml
[build]
  command = "npm run build"

[build.environment]
  NODE_VERSION = "20"

# Netlify auto-detects Next.js and uses OpenNext - no publish/functions config needed
```

- Do NOT set `publish` – Netlify auto-handles Next.js output
- Do NOT add `[[plugins]]` – OpenNext is applied automatically

## Deploy

```bash
npm run build
netlify deploy --prod
```

When prompted, choose **Create & configure a new project** or link to an existing site.
